---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="How fifa2026squads.com is built, where the data comes from, and the trust contract behind 'updated 8 min ago'."
>
  <article class="container-page max-w-reading py-10 sm:py-14">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tightish sm:text-4xl">About</h1>

    <p class="mt-4 text-ink-600 dark:text-ink-300">
      fifa2026squads.com is a single-purpose, daily-refreshed reference site for every player in
      every squad at the 2026 FIFA World Cup, with baseline availability for every player and sourced
      injury, doubtful, suspension, and yellow-card updates when they are present. It also exposes a
      free read-only JSON API and an MCP server so AI agents can consume the same data.
    </p>

    <h2 id="methodology" class="mt-10 text-lg font-semibold">Methodology</h2>
    <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-ink-200">
      <li><strong class="font-semibold">Squad data:</strong> Wikipedia tournament-squad article, enriched per-player from Wikidata. Refreshed weekly and any time a squad is amended.</li>
      <li><strong class="font-semibold">Photos:</strong> Wikimedia Commons; license &amp; photographer credited on every profile page.</li>
      <li><strong class="font-semibold">Status overlay:</strong> Every player has an explicit baseline availability record. Sourced injury, doubtful, suspension, and yellow-card updates replace that baseline as the scanner records them.</li>
      <li><strong class="font-semibold">Trust contract:</strong> Every non-static fact carries a timestamp and a source link. If the &ldquo;updated 8 min ago&rdquo; claim becomes stale, treat that as a bug, not a feature.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="status" class="mt-10 text-lg font-semibold">Status legend</h2>
    <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm">
      <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="badge badge-available"><span class="badge-dot dot-available"></span>Available</span><span class="text-ink-600 dark:text-ink-300">Fit and selectable for next fixture.</span></li>
      <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="badge badge-yellow"><span class="badge-dot dot-yellow"></span>One yellow</span><span class="text-ink-600 dark:text-ink-300">One booking away from a suspension.</span></li>
      <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="badge badge-doubtful"><span class="badge-dot dot-doubtful"></span>Doubtful</span><span class="text-ink-600 dark:text-ink-300">Fitness concern; assessed daily.</span></li>
      <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="badge badge-injured"><span class="badge-dot dot-injured"></span>Injured</span><span class="text-ink-600 dark:text-ink-300">Ruled out of next match.</span></li>
      <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="badge badge-suspended"><span class="badge-dot dot-suspended"></span>Suspended</span><span class="text-ink-600 dark:text-ink-300">Banned from next match.</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="sources" class="mt-10 text-lg font-semibold">Sources &amp; attribution</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-600 dark:text-ink-300">
      Squad and biographical data is derived from Wikipedia and Wikidata, available under
      <a class="prose-link" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CC BY-SA 3.0</a>.
      Player photos are sourced from Wikimedia Commons; the photographer credit and license is
      shown on each player&apos;s profile page.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-600 dark:text-ink-300">
      Not affiliated with FIFA, any national association, or any club mentioned on this site.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-10 text-lg font-semibold">Contact</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-600 dark:text-ink-300">
      Mistakes, requests, partnership: <a class="prose-link" href="mailto:hi@fifa2026squads.com">hi@fifa2026squads.com</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
